  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Using Collective Intelligence to Reduce Analytical Bias and Introduce Local Participation in Designing Humanitarian Response in Drought-Affected Displacement</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this global project, the Nesta Collective Intelligence experiment led by IOM is developing and testing a prototype platform that employs collective intelligence to achieve better targeted and inclusive humanitarian response outcomes. The platform will draw from varied data sources and elaborate possible response options, which in turn can be vetted by multiple users, including local affected populations.</narrative>
  </description>
